quran[16]{c,v,t,f}:
  38,1,"Sād<sup>1</sup>. By the Qur’an, full of reminder<sup>2</sup>,","[1] See footnote 2:1.\n [2] The oath's completion is that the Qur’an is inimitable and thus Allah's miracle."
  38,2,"yet those who disbelieve are in arrogance and dissension.",""
  38,3,"How many generations have We destroyed before them, and they cried out when it was too late for deliverance.",""
  38,4,"They wonder that a warner has come to them from among themselves<sup>3</sup>, and the disbelievers say, “This is a magician and a liar!","[3] The disbelievers demanded that an angel be sent to them to convey the message of Allah, not a human like themselves."
  38,5,"Has he made all gods into one God? Indeed, this is something strange!”",""
  38,6,"The leaders among them departed, saying, “Carry on as you are, and stay faithful to your gods. Indeed, there is a motive behind it<sup>4</sup>.","[4] i.e., The Prophet (ﷺ) only wants to gain influence and prestige for himself."
  38,7,"We have not heard of this in the last religion<sup>5</sup>. This is nothing but a fabrication.","[5] It refers to Christianity or pagan Arab beliefs."
  38,8,"Has the Reminder been sent down to him from among us?” Rather, they are in doubt about My Reminder<sup>6</sup>, for they have not yet tasted My punishment.","[6] They do not question the Prophet's (ﷺ) honesty; rather, they question the Qur’an itself. See 6:33."
  38,9,"Or do they possess the treasuries of the mercy of your Lord, the All-Mighty, the Bestower?",""
  38,10,"Or do they have the dominion of the heavens and earth and all that is between them? Then let them ascend by any means<sup>7</sup>.","[7] To manage the affairs of their dominion."
  38,11,"This is only a small army<sup>8</sup> among several armies<sup>9</sup> that will soon be defeated.","[8] It alludes to the defeat of the pagans of Makkah at Badr.\n [9] i.e., the defeated armies of the past who rejected their messengers."
  38,12,"The people of Noah rejected [their messengers] before them, as did ‘Aad and Pharaoh, the owner of stakes<sup>10</sup>;","[10] It refers to the stakes by which he used to torture people, or the pyramids which are like stakes into the earth."
  38,13,"and Thamūd and the people of Lot, and the dwellers of the Forest – such were the [denier] parties.",""
  38,14,"Each of them rejected their messenger, therefore My punishment became inevitable.",""
  38,15,"They are only waiting for a single Blast that cannot be stopped<sup>11</sup>.","[11] Fawāq: ""respite"", more literally, ""a period between two milkings of a she-camel,"" which also alludes to ""return"" or ""repetition."""
  38,16,"They say, “Our Lord, hasten for us our share [of punishment] before the Day of Reckoning.”",""
